A little story time: Almost two years back, my PCOs was on peak and I was facing massive hair fall issues, to an extent that I had a small bad patch in my mid hairline and all I was doing was ranting about it initially. But along with some supplements and lifestyle changes, these haircare practices really really uplifted my hair health. 

1)Double shampooing: Always remember a clean scalp is the foundation to healthy hair. There’s no thumb rule for the number of times you should be washing your hair. I have extremely oily scalp and dry ends, hence double shampooing is really very important for me. First rinse is always a clarifying shampoo, and second one is a conditioning shampoo only on the hair length 

2) Hair mask as a pre wash treatment: Hairmasks are always better for me rather than conditioners. Since I have low porosity thin fine hair texture, I use hair mask on my damp hair and wear a spa cap for 15 mins and then wash my hair. This gives me the smoothest possible hair. 

3) Scalp scrubbing: Oily scalps are always prone to scalp buildups more. Hence the reason I started scalp scrubbing. It clarifies your scalp and lets your follicles breathe and flourish 

4) Hair growth serums: I’ve tried tons of hair growth serums from the Indian market but these two have worked wonders for me. The only key is to use them religiously without a fail. Also nothing changes overnight. Be patient. 

5) Scalp massage: As much as it is beneficial for the scalp health, hence promoting new hair growth by felicitating blood flow, I find it really really relaxing too. I do this 2-3 times a week. 
.
.

You would be investing in the best skincare and haircare products, following all the viral routines- but still seeing skin irritation, hair fall, hair breakage, and scalp issues, and it’s all because you need to fix your water- the hard water. 

Hard water is loaded with heavy metals, chlorine and other impurities and is the potential culprit for your stubborn hair and skin problems. No serum or deep conditioners would fully work on your hair and skin if your water is not conditioned. 

This hard water filter from @waterscienceindia softens the water, filters out harsh chemicals and creates a clean and balanced base so your skincare and haircare can finally do their job. If your results have been plateaued despite trying everything for your skin and hair, maybe it’s high time to fix your water
